Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how the DMARC Testing Extension ("AntiSpoof") handles your data. By using the Extension, you agree to the terms outlined in this policy.

Data Collection and Usage
No Personal Data Collection: This Extension does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information.
Local Operations: All DMARC validation and testing occur locally on your device. No data is sent to external servers.
No Tracking: The Extension does not track your activity or usage in any way.
Permissions
The Extension may request certain browser permissions to function correctly, such as:

Access to DNS lookup tools for validating DMARC records.
These permissions are solely for providing the intended functionality and are not used for any other purpose.

Third-Party Services
This Extension does not integrate with any third-party services or share data with external entities.

Security
We prioritize the security of your data. Since no personal or sensitive information is collected, the risk to your data is minimal.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes to our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. Please review this page periodically for updates.

Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, feel free to contact us:
